  <thing id="ioMPARCANO" name="ARCANOBOTS Action Figure" description="ARCANOBOTS action figures are durable, articulated, collectible robots powered by magic (though to most of the world, this is just marketing hyperbole). When powered by magic batteries (as opposed to normal batteries), they respond to the verbal commands of their owners. They come equipped with pop-out jet wings and miniature “death ray” guns that deal light sonic/ concussion damage (unless powered by normal batteries, in which case they fire harmless beams of light).\n \nAn ARCANOBOT filled with magic batteries operates for 24 hours, at which point it becomes an inanimate, normal toy.\n \nMagic batteries can be obtained from the manufacturer’s web site ($120,000); most visitors to the web site (who don’t recognize the arcanobots’ true magical nature) assume that the high-cost “magic” batteries are a joke or publicity stunt. Only those with a true understanding of Shadow are likely to pay the price to unlock the Arcanobots actual potential. An ARCANOBOT action figure has the following statistics:\n \nArcanobot: CR 1/4; Diminutive construct; HD 1/8d10; hp 1; Init +3; Spd 10 ft., fly 30 ft. (good); AC 17, touch 17, flat-footed 14 (+3 Dex, +4 size); BAB +0; CMB –16; CMB –17; Atk +0 melee (1d2–4 nonlethal, unarmed strike) or +3 ranged touch (1d3 sonic/concussion, “death ray”); Full Atk +0 melee (1d2–4 nonlethal, unarmed strike) or +3 ranged touch (1d3 sonic/concussion, “death ray”); FS 1 ft. by 1 ft.; Reach 0 ft.; SQ darkvision 60 ft., construct immunities; AL creator or owner; SV Fort +0, Ref +3, Will –5; Str 3, Dex 16, Con —, Int —, Wis 1, Cha 1." compset="Wondrous" stacking="merge">
