  <thing id="ioMPAStkPs" name="Stick of Passes" description="This small usb stick when carried somewhere on your body will automatically enter your user name and password into any computer system with which you are physically interacting with. You must be touching the computer system with your skin, ie hands on a keyboard or mouse. If you are wearing gloves it will not work. \n\nIf you enter a site for which you have no credentials when you go to the create account page a username and password will automatically be created for you. \n\nThe information on the usb stick can be backed up to a computer so that you do not lose your passwords should you lose the usb stick. \nThe backed up information can only be downloaded onto the same or another Stick of Passes. A Stick of Passes is attuned to the person who first uses it and obtaining someone else&apos;s Stick of Passes will not allow you to log in using their credentials; it will simple not function. Saying an activation word will wipe a Stick and attune it to you." compset="Wondrous" holdable="no">
    <comment/>
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="10000"/>
    <fieldval field="iCL" value="10"/>
    <usesource source="D20Arcana"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Wonder"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioMPATieIn" name="Tie of Metal Invisibility" description="This is a thin flexible tie similar to those used to secure toys to their packaging. When tied around a metal object and the other end tied around a body part (it must be touching the skin to function) the metal object is undetectable by metal detectors or body scanning machines. \n\nThe tie does not change the appearance of the metal item so it can still be seen or felt during a physical examination." compset="Wondrous" holdable="no">
