  <thing id="spMPASatTk" name="Satellite Tracking" description="{b}Skill Check{/b}: Spellcraft DC 34, 6 successes, and Knowledge (technology) DC 34, 2 successes\n{b}Sanity Check{/b}: \n{b}Failure{/b}: Two consecutive failed skill checks \n{b}Failure Effect{/b}: Falsehood. The caster obtains bogus GPS data. At the GM&apos;s discretion, the bogus data may lead the caster to a creature or object thematically similar to the intended target\n{b}Material Component{/b}: \n{b}Focus{/b}: A satellite dish, computer, and telemetry software ($1,200)\n{b}Secondary Casters{/b}: \n{b}Spellblight{/b}: Will Save DC 23\n\nA satellite tracking ritual incantation is among the most powerful means of locating creatures or objects. You learn the exact location of a single individual or object. Satellite tracking circumvents normal means of protection from scrying or location.\n\nThe ritual incantation reveals global positioning system (GPS) coordinates for the subject, and a successful computer search (Knowledge (technology) check, DC 10) supplies the name of the location (place, name, business name, building name, or the like), community, county (or similar political division), and country where the subject lies.\n\nTo find a creature with the spell, you must have seen the creature or have some item that once belonged to it. To find an object, you must have touched the object at least once." compset="Spell">
